This was my first time visiting an all vegan establishment and let me tell you, the food was fantastic! Ordering online was a breeze, and pick up was super quick. The lady who helped me out was very sweet. It is safe to say I will be coming back more frequently.
I wish I could give you ZERO for the taste of your food! Guys, avoid this place!!

I’m hungry and very disappointed after ordering food at Shangri-La. Waisted time and money! I would highly recommend avoiding this place!! Tofu Teriyaki and BBQ Ribs taste disgusting; sauce looks like snot and the only taste of the meals was too sweet and rubbery  which is not edible. Maybe your cook making food props for the movie and that’s why he/she doesn’t care about the taste of the meals at all. Kimchee-oversalted! Also, I’ve asked about a glass of hot/warm water but they told me they don’t have it.

I love the food at Shangri-La. It is by far the best vegan Asian cuisine I’ve ever had. Please call instead of using a delivery app to help support this local business, you’ll be glad you did. The staff is always so warm and friendly. They even give you a free face mask with your order which is such a sweet touch. I always order the hot and spicy kimchi sautéed udon with soy protein. It’s fiery and oh so delicious. I’d give the restaurant 10 stars if I could.
This is amazing vegan food! Every single thing I've had here is good. I've only had delivery, never dined in but their delivery customer service is great.
They are so nice.Food is so delicious and they always give free items.plus a free mask!
Never have we had a bad dish. The food it’s always delicious and fresh. Everything has so much flavor! The best part is all vegan!!! Nothing needs to be customized.
I am a fan of their Hot n Sour soup. It's rich in flavor plus ingredients. Tempura was amazing too. 🤘 Clean and good packing for to go.
Very quick service with a few extras thrown in! Also gave us some masks! Food was delicious 😋

Wonderful vegan Chinese restaurant located in a prime Bay Ridge location. The menu is expansive and should appeal to die-hard vegan palates and also people that want it once in a while. The food is delicious here...haven't had anything that I didn't like...and this is someone that enjoys a nice steak! Our favorite dish is their Mapo Tofu! Definitely a place that is a must visit! They also have juices and drinks and a Lunch menu that's a steal!

I almost ordered on Grubhub and decided to instead order over the phone to give business without the ‘middle man.’ The lady who took my order was extremely sweet and helped me swiftly. The food was amazing and they even gave us a complimentary steam veggie dumpling order which was so sweet. I got a Padthai and 2 orders of general tso’s chicken, and ordered one spicy and one extra spicy. The order was perfect and I could tell they listened to my request for an Extra spicy order. Worth the money for it and I got my money’s worth for the food. I would definitely return, thank you for the good experience ! I love trying vegan foods and especially being lactose intolerant, it really gives me peace to know what’s in my food.  Also the lady gave me a free face mask in an envelope, so sweet!
Food was really tasty and filling. I even had a vegetarian skeptic say they wished they had tried the place sooner.
They wouldn’t let me order steak

Honestly a late review since I’ve dined at this place a few times and since Covid began, I have been ordering delivery from them. This restaurant is one of my favorites in Bay Ridge. There are not many vegetarian spots around. Their food is always great and never disappoints. Food was packaged nicely for delivery. I recommend the Mango Avocado Cucumber roll- it is de-li-cious. For our most recent delivery, they included complimentary masks in the bag. Really appreciated that!

Absolutely Delicious! this is My 4th or 5th Time going! the Selections & Varieties to Choose from are Extensive! As well as Affordable! Furthermore, the Food Quality is Extremely Appetizing. This is Definitely A Must Try if You Enjoy ASIATIC, Chinese Dishes...🉑️🎎❤🥡🇨🇳🥡💛🎎㊗️

Absolutely delicious vegetarian food.  If you're an avid meat eater, I wholeheartedly recommend this place. Their soy protein is an unbelievable chicken substitute, with a deliciously satisfying texture.  Try the soy protein with garlic sauce or curry stew - they're both spicy, filling, and amazing, and they're one of the few places that makes impeccable brown rice (not dry at all, and quite hearty).  I've been doing a lot of cooking because of the coronavirus situation, but I've started ordering out from some of Bay Ridge's amazing restaurants, including Shangri-La, Zio Toto, Gino's, etc., for the first time in months - everything I get, I make sure can be heated.  On top of the excellent meal, the folks at Shangri-La packed an envelope with my order, containing a face mask and note of well-wishes. :')  Overall, a phenomenal restaurant with very big-hearted proprietors and talented chefs.
Very good vegan food.
(Translated by Google) Chinese food very exquisite.  (Original) Comida china muy exquisita.
Reasonable prices. Small plate was delicious.
Delicious vegan BBQ ribs, pan fried dumplings and brownie! I Definitely recommend for people looking for a great vegan restaurant!

Was excited to try out this place,  but the quantity and taste were both subpar for the price. Sauces were negligent - the main item that I've seen brings taste to items like pad thai. Sweet potato noodles were interesting,  but again lacking in taste because of no sauce. Really didnt expect this, very disappointed.
Here’s food Taste not good , nothing special, waiter attitude is not good, not worth spending, do not waste money!if you are vegetarian,you need to find better restaurant!
Love the Moo-Shu!
Very good vegan food and desserts
The scallion pancake is TO DIE FOR!!!! SOOOOO GOOD
Wait staff are not nice, not helpful. Food is good but I'm not coming back there because of the rude employees
Vegan rib tips are amazing and love the peach ginger tea!

Been here a few times... I keep hoping but never come away satisfied. Yesterday I had the curry stew and although the vegetables are ok, (pretty hard to ruin those), if you're charging $15+ for entrees, you might not want to go with curry sauce from a powder packet. Just a tip. I could have stayed home and made that myself.  There's never anything here I'm looking forward to getting. I always get this weird feeling I'm getting a vegetarian TV dinner.  Plus what's with the tiny bowls of rice? Is there a cook from North Korea back there?  And not for nothing but the neighborhood must agree with me because I've never seen more than one other table occupied, even on a weekend. You guys really need to up your game a little. There's a dearth of vegetarian restaurants as it is.
Love it
Says vegetarian but is actually vegan! Prices are very reasonable but the portions are quite big.
Healthy, fresh vegan Asian food!
Great Hot and Sour soup!
Good food Good service 👍🏽

I come here for pickup a couple times a month because I live across the street. My order is always correct. The vegan BBQ ribs are delicious. My Boyfriend likes the cold noodles. Being vegetarian myself I love having this place so conveniently located. Unfortunately I found a hair in my rice today... that turned me off a little bit. However, I still love this place and I’ll still keep coming back. Lol. Always substitute for coconut rice!
Love the food! Great vegan place!
Food was amazing !
Great vegan Asian food.

The food was tasty and fresh, hot food was hot, cold food was cold.  The garlic sauce was a little heavy and left a bit of an aftertaste. Note a slight deception: the prices on the in-house menu are slightly higher ($.50-$1) than the on-line and takeout menu, which is posted on the window.
Vegan and great
I order from here at least once a week. The food is amazing. The peanut butter bomb is the BOMB (no pun intended!)
I loooooved the food, it’s a reasonable price and delicious. I love that they are vegan and the size are generous. Also very quick service.
Good vegan food

This is the spot! Small location but good seating. Food was very fresh and flavorful. If you are a vegetarian this place is a God send. Highly recommend for anyone especially if you like that asian/thai style. The tea options are great (hot and cold) and they had some good stuff in the appetizer menu for my daughter who is a little picky. Waitress was very sweet.  I had the green salad which was a lot bigger than I thought it would be, and the pineapple fried rice, girl had the pad thai, daughter had the fried dumplings, fried tofu ( not like other places, the tofu here is much higher quality and prepared very well.) And ademame.
not frindly

I always order from Shangri-La, but this time around I experience something so painful. I ordered curry wonton and on my first bite i almost broke a tooth due to an extra ingredient, called a rock! I called the restaurant before writing this review but due to the lack of empathy and poor communication I had no other choice. I was looking forward some yummy food and instead I ended with a bad toothache.
Best vegan food in bay ridge

This is a wonderful eating experience when you are gluten free and vegan!  Lots of good choices like pumpkin soup and summer roll.  The pineapple fried rice is great, having lots of veggies in it as well as sweet pineapple.  The staff is quick and courteous! Go, experience and enjoy!
I highly suggest eating out here! I got the macro bowl and a side of steamed pumpkin, which, if you go, get those. GO VEGAN!!!✌️

Sadly disappointed as I have been a vegetarian  for over 20 years and live in Bay Ridge. This is one of the only vegan places around here. The service is always depressing and rude. The ambiance is glum. On a Friday night upon entry to the restaurant, instead of being greeted normally by the waitress, we were told the restaurant closes in one hour so we needed to eat and leave. Despite this, we stayed to eat as we both enjoy their food. I ordered from the in house menu that the waitress gave me. I ordered the pumpkin gazpacho that I have ordered from there several times and when my food arrived it was nothing like the description on the menu. The waitress got defensive and proceeded to argue with me, pulled out they menu and told me I was wrong. When I read the ingredients on the menu to her she then told me they changed the menu and this is the new way they make it. She said it's on the new menu and showed me a take out menu which was not shown to me at the time I ordered. Still she was convinced she was right and told me I didn't know what I was ordering. Then told me she didn't want to argue. I WILL NEVER EAT AT THIS RESTAURANT AGAIN. I can not believe how rude she was. I can not believe how far we have come from good customer service. So disappointed in this place.

My favorite vegan spot in all of NYC. The food is delicious, and you get a good portion for the price. Even better deals during the Lunch Specials! I've been going here every month since they first opened.
Food was good just the teriyaki tofu had too much water in the plate.
Great vegetarian food. Has all the typical Chinese dishes. Large selection of teas. Staff are kind. One of my top favorite restaurants.

My absolute favorite restaurant. Staff is really friendly. I try to go here with my fiance as often as I can.  It's a little more on the expensive side, but you get a large plate and THE best tasting food. So, totally worth it.  If you don't have much money to spare, they have GREAT lunch specials that are very fairly priced.

I don't get to go too often, but when I get to go, it's like a treat for me. My son loves the mint lemonade and my favorite so far, is the passion fruit lemonade. As far as the food goes, I haven't had anything bad yet. Today, I had the vegan BBQ rib lunch special and the smoked teriyaki seitan lunch special. Both were just great. I didn't have room for dessert, but I really love the peanut butter bomb. The waitress didn't even come by once to see if everything was okay, so that was the only negative. They still deserve a five-star in my book. There aren't many vegan restaurants, so I love to support them when they have good food. P.S. Someone reported this place having a C rating a month ago, I just noticed. Going to take a picture of the A rating on the window from inside.

Went here with my (very picky) family and had a good time! The sign says vegetarian but the whole place is actually vegan which is amazing considering the lack of vegan options in Bay Ridge. Was able to choose anything on the menu without ant worries. The place is also kosher which is also good to know if that matters to you. We had the summer rolls and spring rolls as  appetizers and I had the orange seitan with miso on the side. I usually don't expect things to be spicy when they have the little chili pepper next to them on the menu because every other place I've been to it never actually is, but the orange seitan and the General Tso's seitan my partner had actually were! I enjoyed it, but be warned if you're not into spicy food. They also have a fully vegan dessert menu, we got the brownie and the pumpkin cheesecake to share. The only reason this is a 4 star review instead of 5 stars is that the brownie was too hard and the summer rolls were a bit flavorless, and the sauce wasn't my favorite. Overall I do recommend this place as an awesome vegan option in Bay Ridge!
I’ve been here once and the food was delicious. I almost went here once again today unless I noticed an inconspicuous C grade on sanitary inspection. I guess it’s better to avoid.

I tried eyebrow tinting for the first time....great first experience I feel like a Kardashian 😁 I got my eyebrows threaded too great job I'm deff gonna go back .ps I never even heard of eyebrow tinting until I walked in
One of my favorite restaurant! Their menu is so big, everything is so delicious! When we are in Brooklyn we always go there :) highly recommend
Good to have a vegan place nearby. Can be expensive but the lunch deals are good.
Best Vegan food
THE FOOD HERE IS SOOO GOOD. Service was fast. Our waiter was very helpful. So much tasty food to choose from. GREAT VEGAN & VEGETARIAN spot everybody needs to try.

You have to try the ribs.... they are so delicious!  They don't deliver to my neighborhood but I get take out and they will bring it to the car if you call ahead.  Parking is notoriously bad in Bay Ridge.
Great tasting vegan food
The food is delicious,but it's a little pricey. But overall the dining experience was nice.

Only true vegan restaurant in the Bay Ridge area. Tasty creative food. Should be 5 stars but reduced to 3 because of B food rating buy New York Department of Health Inspectors. Asian fusion menu it's completely vegan and believe it or not kosher. Very unique for Bay Ridge

Fresh and healthy Chinese food.  Always light on the oil, but high on flavor.  A lot of basics like their miso soup is executed with a bit more thought and attention.  Usually get the health 3 green, fried mushrooms, and the hijiki salad.  Can't go wrong.

In my opinion, this place offers nothing more than mediocre vegan food; I've tried numerous vegan joints throughout the city, and this one is by far, my least favorite. In addition to the mediocre food, what really upset me was when I saw dried food on my glass....yuck! I really wanted to like this place, but it just didn't workout that way. It is really unfortunate  when restaurants start of so well, and then, just go to freakin hell...
Food was quite good.

Great food at a reasonable price. The portions are just right and I love how they use the ingredients in a way you wouldn't expect. My favorite dishes are the Yaki Udon and the Pad Thai. Great for a light lunch or a casual dinner with friends. The Thai iced tea is also worth a try.

Their Black Pepper Seitan is to DIE for. Soooo so good. The BBQ Ribs however were made like (non-veg) boneless spareribs yet were too soft and chewy to be enjoyable. Choose the salad over the soup, and get coconut rice every time! Also, the takeout portion sizes are very generous & delivery is always fast. 💯
Tasty!
UN -FREAKIN-BELIEVABLE!
First time customer , delicious food, clean, nice place,  awesome music, friendly staff, good prices, will visit again
Great food! A little over priced though!

Amazing veggie-friendly place, great service. Wish they would deliver a little bit further, but so worth the drive. 5/5

They deliver really far - all the way up to Greenwood Cemetery. Great vegetarian/vegan foods. Try the mango appetizer.

wow, we were just visiting and found this place and totally blown away by the food. The curry dish was amazing and the subtlety of the flavors was wonderful. Not overly sweet like many vegan/vegetarian restaurants. Try the pumpkin soup. Loved it.

We come from Staten Island on a weekly basis!! The food is always fresh and perfectly cooked!! Love the Black Pepper Seitan, and always start with the Pumpkin Soup! A great healthy alternative!! Vegan Delicious!! A must try!!

Excellent all-Vegan menu, thats not too different as to scare off meat eaters. Trick is simple "seitan" replaces "beef," and "soy protein" replaces chicken. There, now you know how to order. For dessert- the peanut butter bomb is, just as it sounds, "THE BOMB"
Everything we have tried has been exceptionally good. I must have my weekly fix.

Wow! That's all! I'm in food heaven!
Best vegan restaurant in Brooklyn. Don't let the other gross "fake meat " in other Asian restaurants deter  you from trying vegan "meat" This place makes delicious vegan food.
Finally, solid vegetarian and vegan options in my neighborhood! My favorites are the salt and pepper oyster mushrooms, seitan skewers, and peanut butter bomb cake. Reliable delivery is a huge plus.
Only my second time here, and already looking forward to my next time.

Yes, a vegetarian restaurant in Bay Ridge! Everything here is a great - especially the more unusual menu items, like the pumpkin soup or the fried King Oyster mushroom. And the vegan desserts are divine.
